   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1865_05_16_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Kreglinger_Amsterdam_1.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>KREGLINGER &amp; CO<lb/>AMSTERDAM<lb/>SHANGHAI<lb/>1<lb/>JUIL<lb/>65<lb/>FRANCAIS[?]<lb/>via Marseille <lb/>AMSTERDAM<lb/>16/5<lb/>5-9<lb/>65<lb/>P.
                P.<lb/>Messrs.<lb/>FRANCO<lb/>[...]MAI <lb/>65[...] <lb/>L. Kniffler + Co. <lb/>AMSTERDAM<lb/>16/5<lb/>12-5<lb/>65<lb/>KREGLINGER &amp; CO. <lb/>AMSTERDAM<lb/>Japan
                Nagasaki<lb/>⟨1865<lb/>Amsterdam 16/5<lb/>Kreglinger +Co.<lb/>R⟩</p>
         <pb facs="1865_05_16_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Kreglinger_Amsterdam_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>Amsterdam 16th May 1865<lb/>Messsrs. L. Kniffler + Co.<lb/>Nagasaki Japan<lb/>We confirm for you our respectful last letter <lb/>from 9th Feb and have received your esteemed letter
                <lb/>from 9th March, from which we are pleased to see the<lb/>confirmation of the current account sent to you. <lb/>In terms of shipping matters we have notified you <lb/>of the
                following shipments <lb/>5th April on the “Jacqueline-Elise” under captain I. H. Krukkenberg<lb/>
            <table>
               <row>
                  <cell>D[ubbers] </cell>
                  <cell>27/28</cell>
                  <cell>2 boxes of hats from shipment Messrs. <lb/>N. H. Dubbers, Altona</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>
                     <figure>
                        <figDesc>Company Sign Raschle &amp; Co. Capital letters are separated along the middle of the line with a dividing line. On the dividing line are the letters K + C, underneath it the letter R</figDesc>
                     </figure>
                  </cell>
                  <cell>19/24</cell>
                  <cell>6 " of textiles from shipment <lb/>I. R. Raschle &amp; Co., Wattwyl</cell>
               </row>
            </table> 1st May on the “Julie” under captain Cherpion <table rend="rules">
               <row>
                  <cell>
                     <figure>
                        <figDesc>Company Sign Mechanische Webereien Altstätten. Three-line logo set above, on and below the row, featuring a crutch cross and letters with distincitve serifs. Above the row is the cross ☩, within the row the letters MW and underneath the row the letter A</figDesc>
                     </figure>
                  </cell>
                  <cell>301/304</cell>
                  <cell>4 boxes of textiles from shipment by Mechanische Weberei in Altstätten</cell>
               </row>
            </table> We wish you the safe receipt of these and ask<lb/>that you proceed with them in line with the wishes of<lb/>the respective senders.<lb/>About our market we have nothing
                significant <lb/>to report. <lb/>The insert we ask you to forward to your <lb/>company in Yokohama.<lb/>We sign Yours respectfully <lb/>Kreglinger +Co.</p>
         <pb facs="1865_05_16_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Kreglinger_Amsterdam_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1865_05_16_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Kreglinger_Amsterdam_4.tif" n="4"/>
      </body>
   </text>
